about how I owe you my life.

981
01:07:36,304 --> 01:07:39,349
- He almost killed you.
- You jealous ?

982
01:07:39,599 --> 01:07:41,726
You wanted to know what it was like.

983
01:07:41,976 --> 01:07:43,269
What what was like ?

984
01:07:43,520 --> 01:07:46,189
The great lesson
of being close to death.

985
01:07:46,439 --> 01:07:47,816
Know what I know ?

986
01:07:48,108 --> 01:07:50,110
Same thing you know.

987
01:07:50,485 --> 01:07:52,195
We're in a real bad way.

988
01:08:14,342 --> 01:08:15,969
Fuck.

989
01:08:17,721 --> 01:08:19,347
Real bad way.

990
01:08:19,597 --> 01:08:21,933
AII right ! Let's go ! Move it !

991
01:08:22,183 --> 01:08:23,393
Come on ! Let's go !

992
01:08:23,727 --> 01:08:26,062
- Come on ! Move ! Move !
 Move your ass !

993
01:08:26,312 --> 01:08:28,273
Come on, fat boy ! Move your ass !

994
01:08:28,523 --> 01:08:30,358
Let's go, soldier !

995
01:08:36,031 --> 01:08:37,657
Let's go ! Let's go !

996
01:08:42,078 --> 01:08:43,413
C.O.Welcome to Tigerland !

997
01:08:43,663 --> 01:08:46,666
Your final training
before you're shipped overseas !

998
01:08:46,916 --> 01:08:49,878
Here, everything's done
exactly as it is over there.

999
01:08:50,170 --> 01:08:52,756
You will search and destroy,
hunt and kill !

1000
01:08:53,006 --> 01:08:56,301
You'll move by chopper to secure
any area deemed necessary.

1001
01:08:56,509 --> 01:08:58,553
You'll be allowed one hour's sleep.

1002
01:08:58,762 --> 01:09:01,431
Minor mistakes
will pay back major punishment.

1003
01:09:01,639 --> 01:09:04,017
Maybe you've heard
we've lost this war.

1004
01:09:04,351 --> 01:09:07,312
Or we've lost the support
of people here at home.

1005
01:09:07,562 --> 01:09:09,606
It's too late to
ask those questions.

1006
01:09:09,939 --> 01:09:11,733
You're not back on the block.

1007
01:09:11,941 --> 01:09:14,611
You're alive in a year,
we'll talk about it.

1008
01:09:14,861 --> 01:09:16,363
When you arrive in Nam....

1009
01:09:16,571 --> 01:09:19,616
....it's important to get acclimated
as quickly as you can.

1010
01:09:19,908 --> 01:09:21,951
Remember to think.

1011
01:09:22,160 --> 01:09:24,287
- You understand me ?
- Yes, sergeant !

1012
01:09:24,537 --> 01:09:29,584
What matters now is sharpening your
ability to find and destroy the enemy.

1013
01:09:29,834 --> 01:09:31,544
Practice how to stay alive.

1014
01:09:31,795 --> 01:09:35,256
I know what you're thinking.
I've been there myself.

1015
01:09:35,840 --> 01:09:38,385
You're thinking you'll
go somewhere safe.

1016
01:09:38,635 --> 01:09:39,803
You'll luck out.

1017
01:09:40,095 --> 01:09:43,348
Tigerland is where
you stop bullshitting yourself.

1018
01:09:43,598 --> 01:09:47,435
Sarge, you got any advice
on how to stay alive in Vietnam ?

1019
01:09:47,686 --> 01:09:50,438
I do, private. Don't go.
- Right on, right on.

1020
01:09:50,689 --> 01:09:53,066
My friend here wants the experience.

1021
01:09:53,400 --> 01:09:55,193
Says he ain't scared.

1022
01:09:55,527 --> 01:09:57,320
Well, good luck.

1023
01:09:57,529 --> 01:10:01,199
If you ask me, I'll stick
with the smart and the scared.

1024
01:10:01,408 --> 01:10:06,371
You'll be under the care of NCOs
and officers who were in combat.

1025
01:10:06,663 --> 01:10:08,248
Listen to them.

1026
01:10:08,456 --> 01:10:11,710
They know what they're talking about.
Cota.

1027
01:10:12,961 --> 01:10:14,754
I'm Staff Sergeant Cota.

1028
01:10:15,005 --> 01:10:16,965
I've done two tours in Vietnam.

1029
01:10:17,173 --> 01:10:19,843
My first in '67 with the 101 st.

1030
01:10:20,301 --> 01:10:23,096
Ijust completed my second with MAC-V.

1031
01:10:23,346 --> 01:10:26,141
I only have two words
of advice for you.

1032
01:10:26,391 --> 01:10:28,101
And those are to listen... 

1033
01:10:28,518 --> 01:10:29,811
... and to learn.

1034
01:10:30,979 --> 01:10:33,231
AII right, let's saddle up.

1035
01:10:34,065 --> 01:10:36,151
Let's go ! Let's saddle up !

1036
01:10:36,401 --> 01:10:37,902
Let's go, goddamn it !

1037
01:10:41,948 --> 01:10:43,616
Get down !

1038
01:10:43,825 --> 01:10:46,327
Good job, Paxton. Good job.

1039
01:10:46,578 --> 01:10:48,163
Good job, Johnson.

1040
01:10:48,371 --> 01:10:49,456
AII right.

1041
01:10:49,706 --> 01:10:51,624
Get your ass behind that tree !

1042
01:10:51,833 --> 01:10:55,712
Fantastic. You guys move
like fucking soldiers !

1043
01:10:56,212 --> 01:10:58,173
Get your ass down !

1044
01:10:59,299 --> 01:11:00,884
Ryan, get your ass down !

1045
01:11:01,176 --> 01:11:03,303
Go ! Move ! Move !

1046
01:11:03,595 --> 01:11:06,139
Bozz, keep that barrel
out of the dirt !

1047
01:11:06,348 --> 01:11:07,599
Move, move, move !

1048
01:11:07,807 --> 01:11:10,101
Paxton, why are you slowing up ?

1049
01:11:10,310 --> 01:11:11,770
Get your ass down !

1050
01:11:12,479 --> 01:11:14,356
You are the weak link !

1051
01:11:14,731 --> 01:11:17,108
This is not the time to slow up.

1052
01:11:17,317 --> 01:11:19,194
Adapt ! Overcome !

1053
01:11:19,444 --> 01:11:21,112
Move ! Get in there !

1054
01:11:22,489 --> 01:11:23,531
You good ?

1055
01:11:23,740 --> 01:11:25,575
Why were you slow, Paxton ?

1056
01:11:25,825 --> 01:11:28,661
- Are you hurt ?
- No, I'm fine, sergeant.

1057
01:11:39,881 --> 01:11:41,549
Diagonal, Private Barnes.

1058
01:11:41,841 --> 01:11:44,803
- So you don't chop your knee off.
- Yes, sergeant.

1059
01:11:50,350 --> 01:11:53,269
Go ahead, Paxton.
I gotta take a piss.

1060
01:11:54,354 --> 01:11:56,189
- You okay ?
- Yeah.

1061
01:12:54,414 --> 01:12:57,459
"Jim Paxton
on personal guide to pain. "

1062
01:12:59,836 --> 01:13:03,840
Get that fucking torch out of my face
and put that cigarette out.

1063
01:13:04,049 --> 01:13:07,177
You might as well
hang a big neon sign that says:

1064
01:13:07,385 --> 01:13:09,512
"Dumb-fuck grunts, right here. "

1065
01:13:09,804 --> 01:13:12,724
You broke light discipline.
Therefore, you're dead.

1066
01:13:12,974 --> 01:13:15,018
- Do you understand ?
 Yes.

1067
01:13:15,226 --> 01:13:18,146
- Good.
 I'm still alive, sergeant.

1068
01:13:18,521 --> 01:13:21,691
- What did you say ?
- I said, I'm still alive.

1069
01:13:22,192 --> 01:13:25,236
I miraculously survived the attack.

1070
01:13:25,612 --> 01:13:27,530
- You didn't get hit ?
- No.

1071
01:13:27,739 --> 01:13:29,115
Are your friends alive ?

1072
01:13:29,366 --> 01:13:32,327
Yeah, Paxton's good.
Johnson, he's good and he's good.

1073
01:13:32,660 --> 01:13:36,081
If you're gonna make up a story,
make up a happy one.

1074
01:13:36,956 --> 01:13:39,167
I ain't making anything up, son.

1075
01:13:42,170 --> 01:13:45,799
And in Vietnam there are no
happy fucking stories.

1076
01:13:52,555 --> 01:13:55,475
I had a best buddy, Kelly Morgan....

1077
01:13:55,767 --> 01:13:58,812
....that I went to AIT with.

1078
01:14:00,772 --> 01:14:04,609
In'67, when the call came,
we got sent off to Nam.

1079
01:14:05,235 --> 01:14:09,864
We had only been in country
a few days. We was green as grass.

1080
01:14:11,157 --> 01:14:15,286
We were in a two-man listening post,
talking just like we are here.

1081
01:14:15,954 --> 01:14:18,206
Kelly lit up a cigarette.

1082
01:14:19,082 --> 01:14:21,793
One minute we're naming
his unborn child....

1083
01:14:22,002 --> 01:14:25,672
....and the next second
his brains were in my lap.

1084
01:14:37,726 --> 01:14:41,396
The sniper zeroed in
on the cherry of his cigarette, Bozz.

1085
01:14:46,026 --> 01:14:49,654
Gentlemen, it's all about respect.

1086
01:14:50,780 --> 01:14:54,451
Respect for your superiors
and what they're trying to teach you.

1087
01:14:55,744 --> 01:14:59,080
Respect for yourselves and your unit.

1088
01:15:00,790 --> 01:15:02,834
And most important....

1089
01:15:04,294 --> 01:15:06,171
....respect the enemy.

1090
01:15:11,843 --> 01:15:14,095
You have 42 minutes....

1091
01:15:14,346 --> 01:15:16,973
....then the squad's on patrol.

1092
01:15:22,228 --> 01:15:23,480
Fuck.

1093
01:15:30,570 --> 01:15:34,949
Gentlemen, this is the best Vietnamese
village we could create for you....

1094
01:15:35,200 --> 01:15:36,409
....here on the base !

1095
01:15:36,701 --> 01:15:40,705
Now, listen. You're all gooks,
so nobody speaks English.

1096
01:15:40,914 --> 01:15:44,626
Anybody asks you a question
in English, you answer, "No bic. "

1097
01:15:44,918 --> 01:15:47,420
It means, "I don't speak" in gook-ese.
Let's hear it.

1098
01:15:47,671 --> 01:15:48,672
No bic.

1099
01:15:48,880 --> 01:15:52,467
Good. Private Bozz, you are
the only man that speaks English.

1100
01:15:52,759 --> 01:15:57,806
Speak only to the man who identifies
himself as interpreter. Understood ?

1101
01:15:58,014 --> 01:15:59,808
- Yes, sir.
- Good. Private Paxton.

1102
01:16:00,058 --> 01:16:01,518
You are the Vietcong.

1103
01:16:01,768 --> 01:16:06,439
They come through, their objective
is to find the VC sympathizer.

1104
01:16:06,648 --> 01:16:09,192
In other words, you, Private Paxton.

1105
01:16:09,442 --> 01:16:11,444
They have five minutes.

1106
01:16:11,653 --> 01:16:14,781
You tell them nothing.

1107
01:16:15,281 --> 01:16:16,908
I warn you, they're beat up.

1108
01:16:17,158 --> 01:16:18,993
They've been awake three nights.

1109
01:16:19,327 --> 01:16:20,870
Forced marched all day.

1110
01:16:21,121 --> 01:16:25,208
They fuck this up,
they'll march another six miles.

1111
01:16:25,417 --> 01:16:26,710
One other thing:

1112
01:16:26,960 --> 01:16:30,839
They find out
which one of you is VC... 

1113
01:16:31,047 --> 01:16:33,758
... and you'll be the ones
out in the boonies... 

1114
01:16:33,967 --> 01:16:37,345
... on no sleep, forced marching
for the next two nights.

1115
01:16:37,595 --> 01:16:38,638
Understood ?

1116
01:16:38,888 --> 01:16:40,849
- Yes, sergeant.
- Let's get to work.

1117
01:16:41,141 --> 01:16:43,768
Private Bozz, Paxton. Over here.

1118
01:16:44,060 --> 01:16:47,480
Lets see...... 
Lukins, Barnes, in this hooch.

1119
01:16:47,814 --> 01:16:50,025
Make it as realistic as possible.

1120
01:16:50,191 --> 01:16:52,527
This is not a fucking joke.

1121
01:16:52,777 --> 01:16:55,280
I like this.
It's like a war theme park.

1122
01:16:55,488 --> 01:16:58,199
I'm so tired. I'm gonna pass out.

1123
01:17:08,918 --> 01:17:11,254
Hey, here they come.

1124
01:17:16,760 --> 01:17:18,136
Shit.

1125
01:17:18,428 --> 01:17:19,679
It's Wilson.

1126
01:17:20,847 --> 01:17:22,098
What ?

1127
01:17:22,349 --> 01:17:25,977
- I thought we got him out.
- There's a war going on.

1128
01:17:26,186 --> 01:17:28,605
Plenty of room
for psychopathic killers.

1129
01:17:28,813 --> 01:17:31,358
Let's move it.
We don't got much time.

1130
01:17:31,649 --> 01:17:34,027
We gotta find the VC.

1131
01:17:37,447 --> 01:17:38,740
No bic.

1132
01:17:39,407 --> 01:17:41,117
Fuck me.

1133
01:17:43,078 --> 01:17:44,329
- VC ?
- No bic.

1134
01:17:45,955 --> 01:17:48,208
- Get your ass on the ground !
- No bic.

1135
01:17:48,416 --> 01:17:50,543
- No bic.
- No bic. No bic.

1136
01:17:52,587 --> 01:17:54,464
Get on the fucking ground !

1137
01:17:55,048 --> 01:17:56,549
- You VC ?
- No bic.

1138
01:17:57,634 --> 01:17:59,010
- You VC ?
- No bic.

1139
01:17:59,260 --> 01:18:00,261
- You VC ?
- No bic.

1140
01:18:00,595 --> 01:18:01,721
How'd that feel ?

1141
01:18:02,013 --> 01:18:06,351
Need an interpreter ?
I'm the only one that speaks English.

1142
01:18:09,354 --> 01:18:11,064
How does that feel, Paxton ?

1143
01:18:17,570 --> 01:18:19,698
What are you gonna write about now ?

1144
01:18:24,244 --> 01:18:26,454
What are you writing in your journal ?

1145
01:18:32,544 --> 01:18:33,920
Don't fucking move !

1146
01:18:35,839 --> 01:18:38,216
Let go of him, goddamn it !

1147
01:18:44,973 --> 01:18:48,476
- You're in charge ! On your feet !
- Yes, sergeant.

1148
01:18:48,977 --> 01:18:51,312
Where is your weapon, soldier ?

1149
01:18:51,563 --> 01:18:52,814
There it is.

1150
01:18:53,106 --> 01:18:56,359
Why didn't you secure the area,
Private Wilson ?

1151
01:18:56,901 --> 01:19:00,488
I'll tell you why.
Because you lost control !

1152
01:19:00,739 --> 01:19:02,240
Yes, sergeant.

1153
01:19:03,283 --> 01:19:05,618
Did you find any VC ?

1154
01:19:05,869 --> 01:19:09,748
No, you didn't.
That's the fucking answer.

1155
01:19:10,123 --> 01:19:11,416
Come here.

1156
01:19:13,418 --> 01:19:17,714
I promise you tears before breakfast.
Get your men and get out of here.

1157
01:19:17,922 --> 01:19:20,133
Get out of here ! Let's go. Move !

1158
01:19:20,342 --> 01:19:22,594
- I'm gonna kill you.
- Is that right ?

1159
01:19:23,553 --> 01:19:25,847
- You gonna kill me again ?
- I'll kill you.

1160
01:19:26,181 --> 01:19:28,016
Get your hands off him !

1161
01:19:29,476 --> 01:19:31,144
You want to go ?

1162
01:19:31,394 --> 01:19:33,980
Get the fuck out of here !

1163
01:19:38,026 --> 01:19:40,403
- Get the fuck out !
- I'll break your neck !

1164
01:19:40,737 --> 01:19:43,198
- Let's move !
 Get the fuck out of here !

1165
01:19:43,448 --> 01:19:45,116
Somebody grab my steel pot.

1166
01:19:45,367 --> 01:19:47,035
Get out of here.

1167
01:19:47,410 --> 01:19:49,412
- How you doing ?
- Shit.

1168
01:19:49,662 --> 01:19:51,081
Is he all right ?

1169
01:19:51,331 --> 01:19:52,665
No, he's not all right.

1170
01:19:52,916 --> 01:19:55,210
Take your time.

1171
01:21:00,817 --> 01:21:02,861
- You going ?
 I can't take you with me.

1172
01:21:03,153 --> 01:21:05,613
Not me. Paxton. He's hurting.

1173
01:21:05,864 --> 01:21:06,906
He signed up.

1174
01:21:07,198 --> 01:21:08,825
And you judged him for it.

1175
01:21:09,034 --> 01:21:12,120
You even made me feel guilty
and I was drafted.

1176
01:21:16,124 --> 01:21:18,835
You saw what Wilson did to him today.

1177
01:21:20,795 --> 01:21:22,172
He's broken down.

1178
01:21:22,339 --> 01:21:25,175
And the Army didn't do
all the breaking. Take him.

1179
01:21:25,383 --> 01:21:28,511
It's not my fault if he
just realized what he did.

1180
01:21:28,762 --> 01:21:31,139
I only got time for my sad story.

1181
01:21:31,348 --> 01:21:33,850
- Take him with you.
- Fuck off !

1182
01:21:34,059 --> 01:21:36,770
Wilson's gonna take
his hate out on somebody.

1183
01:21:36,978 --> 01:21:41,733
You run, he'll kill Paxton.
If not here, for sure over in Nam.

1184
01:21:42,025 --> 01:21:44,152
Johnson, I like you, but fuck off.

1185
01:21:45,320 --> 01:21:47,781
Yeah, well,
I ain't standing in your way.

1186
01:22:43,461 --> 01:22:45,338
Rise and shine, gentlemen !

1187
01:22:45,547 --> 01:22:47,507
Let's go, gentlemen ! Roll'em !

1188
01:22:47,757 --> 01:22:50,593
Let's go ! Move ! Get on your feet !

1189
01:22:50,760 --> 01:22:55,390
I know you're tired, but you'll be
doing a lot of this in the next year !

1190
01:22:55,640 --> 01:22:57,058
If you're not....

1191
01:22:57,183 --> 01:23:00,145
-....then you're in a body bag.
- Where's Bozz ?

1192
01:23:00,353 --> 01:23:03,106
Waiting for a dust-off.

1193
01:23:03,690 --> 01:23:06,192
Where is your squad leader ?

1194
01:23:06,651 --> 01:23:08,361
Is this his weapon ?

1195
01:23:08,570 --> 01:23:11,448
Does anybody know
where your squad leader is ?

1196
01:23:11,698 --> 01:23:13,074
Where is he, Johnson ?

1197
01:23:19,622 --> 01:23:23,084
- Where is your weapon, Private Bozz ?
- Right here, sarge.

1198
01:23:23,293 --> 01:23:24,544
I know that.

1199
01:23:24,794 --> 01:23:28,465
The next time you decide
to take a piss or a fucking shit....

1200
01:23:28,715 --> 01:23:30,759
....you make sure you have your weapon.

1201
01:23:31,051 --> 01:23:34,387
Your weapon is your lifeline.
Why didn't you have it ?

1202
01:23:34,596 --> 01:23:38,183
I was gonna make a break for Mexico.
I didn't think I'd need it.

1203
01:23:38,433 --> 01:23:39,851
Very funny.

1204
01:23:40,685 --> 01:23:42,354
You take point.

1205
01:23:42,896 --> 01:23:46,858
Paxton, take slack. Johnson, drag.
The rest of you fall in behind.

1206
01:23:47,108 --> 01:23:48,360
Listen up.

1207
01:23:48,610 --> 01:23:52,113
